President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation declaring October 15-21, 2017, as National Forest Products Week. The proclamation recognizes the importance of forest products to our daily lives and the economy, as well as the beauty and recreational opportunities provided by our woodlands. It acknowledges the challenges faced by forests and communities due to wildfires and prays for the safety of people and first responders. The proclamation emphasizes the economic value of forest products, the jobs they create, and their contribution to our everyday lives. It also highlights the need for responsible management and stewardship to ensure the sustainability of our forests for future generations. The President calls upon all Americans to observe the week with appropriate ceremonies and activities and reaffirm our commitment to our Nation's forests.